## 🚫 What NOT to Do with This Model

### ❌ Don't Use to Explain Everything
```
"Our radion mechanism explains dark matter, 
dark energy, inflation, and UAP sightings"
→ This makes us a crackpot. Don't do it.
```

### ❌ Don't Make Vague Predictions
```
"The mechanism might affect X, Y, and Z 
in complicated ways we haven't worked out"
→ This isn't science. We only claim what we derive.
```

### ❌ Don't Defend Bad Claims
```
"JWST LRDs show our model is right 
even though our calculation doesn't work"
→ This is the opposite of the retraction lesson.
Admit failure, refocus, move on.
```

### ❌ Don't Mix Domains
```
"Our 5D gravity model implies lab-scale 
experiments should show exotic effects"
→ Different scales, different physics. Stick to cosmology.
```

